sql:
SELECT COUNT(*) AS completed_workorders_count
FROM maintenance_workorders
WHERE status = 'completed';

SELECT property_id, COUNT(*) AS total_tenants
FROM tenants
GROUP BY property_id;

external_knowledge:
Average completion time refers to the average number of days between the submission of a maintenance request and its completion; 
Maintenance requests with status 'completed' are those that have been finished; 
Properties in Springfield refer to those having 'Springfield' as their city; 
More than 5 maintenance requests indicates that we are only interested in properties that have had at least 6 maintenance requests.

- Payroll to rent ratio = total payroll / average monthly rent; 
- Active leases refer to leases with an end date in the future; 
- The payroll is calculated for the current month.

sql:
SELECT AVG(payment_count) AS average_payments_per_lease
FROM (
  SELECT lease_id, COUNT(*) AS payment_count
  FROM rent_payments
  GROUP BY lease_id
) AS lease_payment_counts;

SELECT SUM(units) AS total_units
FROM properties
WHERE property_id IN (SELECT property_id FROM user_properties WHERE user_id = 0);
